=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_RunningSum_ex2 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 444 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: stable
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 443.8278
  harmonic_decay_rate: -10.7597
  harmonic_regularity: 0.7859
  pitch_clarity: 160.6170
  inharmonicity: 0.0039
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -5.9809
  resonance_freq: 430.6641

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: RunningSum Example 2
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/RunningSum.html
// Tags: RunningSum, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 2 ---
// RMS Power
(
{
    var input, numsamp;

    input = LFSaw.ar;
    numsamp = 30;

    (RunningSum.ar(input.squared, numsamp) / numsamp).sqrt
}.play
)
